Hello, I'm Cynthia.

My journey with wine began unexpectedly. I came to South Florida dreaming of becoming a chef, but while working at a wine shop during culinary school, something clicked. I realized that a good dish is made extraordinary with the right wineand that wine connects history, geography, culture, and people in ways few things can.

Since then, I've had the privilege of serving the King of Spain, building award-winning wine lists at the Mandarin Oriental and The Biltmore, and traveling to wine regions across the globe. I've earned every certification I could get my hands on, won a few awards along the waybut what I love most is sharing that first spark of discovery with someone new to wine.

Advanced Sommelier, CMS WSET Level 3 Level 1 Sake James Beard 2011

My Philosophy

I want you to feel what I felt when I fell in love with this industry: the experience of dining, the music, the service, the aromayet in a simple, fun, approachable way.

Wine doesn't have to be intimidating. It doesn't require a fancy cellar or a sommelier certification. It just requires curiosity and good company. That's what SommOM is all aboutcreating spaces where women can explore, learn, and connect over something beautiful.

My Journey

After graduating from culinary school, I pivoted entirely to wine. I spent years working in Miami's finest restaurantsthe Mandarin Oriental, The Biltmore, Four Seasonsbuilding wine programs and serving guests who taught me just as much as I taught them.

In 2011, I was honored with a James Beard nomination, which felt like validation for years of hard work and passion. But the real reward has always been those moments of connection: watching someone's eyes light up when they finally understand what makes a great Burgundy special, or seeing a group of friends bond over a bottle they'll remember forever.

Today, I bring that same energy to private tastings and tours. No restaurant formality, no pretensionjust genuine passion shared in intimate settings.

Moments & Memories

Let's explore together.

Whether you're just beginning your wine journey or you've been collecting for years, I'd love to share a glass with you.
